notes: The patient has Wilson disease, which is a genetic disorder that can cause liver damage and other complications. The patient's symptoms include tremors, jaundice, hepatosplenomegaly, and hypotonia of the upper limbs. The patient also has aggressive behavior and a constant smile on his face.
